descript.abstract: This line data layer represents roads for Portage County, Wisconsin at year-end 2016. It is a feature clss within the geodatabase, Portage_Roads_YE2016.gdb. The feature layers included in this geodatabase are 'PORTAGE_ROW_YE2016'.[The Centerline data set is a vector representation of center of pavement in the County of Portage, Wisconsin. The centerlines are digitized from 1:12000 digital orthophotography or entered by coordinate geometry.]
descript.purpose:
This layer is intended for reference and mapping purposes, and may be used for basic applications such as viewing, querying, and map output production, or to provide a basemap to support graphical overlays and analysis with other spatial data.
[These data are intended for use at a scale of 1:12000 or smaller. The data are designed for reference mapping and labelling.]
descript.supplinf: The address fields are not populated.

distinfo.custom: Any portion of the data set can be requested. Data can be distributed on 3.5 inch floppy, CD-ROM, or e-mail depending upon file size.

srcinfo.srccontr: Improved horizontal accuracy of roads existing in year 2000.

procstep.procdesc: Centerlines are dgitized from orthophotos when possible. New roads are added using coordinate geometry from surveys or subdivision plats. We use center of right-of-way as centerlines for new roads.

attracc.attraccr: Street names and naming convetions are constantly changing. We update as errors are detected and changes occur. All but the most obscure errors have been rooted out by constant use.

qattracc.attracce: We find about one error per quarter from the E911 / master thoroughfare list.

dataqual.logic: This is a simple chain data set. There are nodes where roads intersect and where road names change. Chains intersect without a node at overpasses.
dataqual.complete: This data set includes all roads in Portage County

horizpa.horizpar: Centerlines are digitized from orthophotography with a scale of 1:12000. Accuracy is similar to the source photo.

qhorizpa.horizpae: National Map Accuracy Standard for 1:12000 source orthophotography
